N.A. Andreacchio's comments were right on target.  As a veteran of three tours in Vietnam and Cambodia (2/70-2/72) I was not an advisor but was part of a small team of Americans assigned to Vietnamese units.  I have seen probably every film so far produced (although there were some I had wished I'd not seen) and I too have always felt that &quot;Go Tell the Spartans&quot; was the best film to date on the war.  It is available on VHS and is well worth seeing.  It shows the war in its early years and was based on a book titled &quot;Incident at Moc Hoa&quot;.  I have been looking for this book.  If any one knows where I might find a copy, I would greatly appreciate it.
